117
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,840
Almost done.

118
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,400
Let me see just how popular it is.

119
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,760
I have an idea,

120
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:53,480
we need to strike while the iron is hot.

121
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,320
What?

122
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,800
Aren't we preparing for this year's Peach Blossom Festival?

123
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,320
I'd like you to create some paintings for the festival

124
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,580
for online promotion.

125
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:01,760
I...

126
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,000
can I really do it?

127
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,080
Of course you can,

128
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:06,920
as long as people like it.

129
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,680
It just proves you're a good artist,

130
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,080
right?

131
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,090
Well,

132
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:13,240
I'll try my best.

133
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:13,760
Give it a try.

134
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,720
Just try it.

135
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,080
It's freshly baked,

136
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,080
eat it while it's hot.

137
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:18,560
Look,

138
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,320
this is so embarrassing.

139
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,720
I knew you didn't have time for breakfast this morning.

140
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,320
We were looking for someone to collaborate with anyway,

141
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,600
and you came at just the right time.

142
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,530
I'll try my best.

143
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,520
You can do it.

144
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,280
Okay.

145
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,560
Ding Nian.

146
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:31,960
I have an idea now,

147
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,400
give me those paintings.

148
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,520
I've been looking at them over and over,

149
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:36,120
and I like them more and more.

150
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:36,920
I think

151
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:37,840
we could turn them into

152
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,360
cultural and creative products.

153
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,159
Like postcards,

154
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:42,960
notebooks, stamps, stickers,

155
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,400
these basic products.

156
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,600
They're quick to make and low-cost,

157
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,240
and young people really love them nowadays.

158
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,840
I love those merchandise items.

159
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,840
You like them too?

160
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:51,480
That's great.

161
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,640
Let's look into it,

162
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,680
study it carefully, come on.

163
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,880
Come,

164
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,360
take it easy, slow down.

165
00:05:59,240 --> 00:05:59,880
Hello.

166
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,840
Could you both please provide your ID cards?

167
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:02,840
I need to register your check-in.

168
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:03,680
We're not in a hurry to check in.

169
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,480
We'd like to get portraits done.

170
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:06,920
No rush, no rush.

171
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,120
Check in first

172
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,480
and put your luggage away.

173
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,080
When you go out later,

174
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,200
take plenty of photos,

175
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,880
choose a nice one and send it to me,

176
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,680
then I'll arrange for your portraits.

177
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,800
I see.

178
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,320
What was that peak called again?

179
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,380
I want that one too.

180
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,360
Namcha Barwa Peak.

181
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,080
Right.

182
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,600
If you want to photograph that scenery, you'll need to take a car.

183
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,280
No, no, no. We want to ride horses.

184
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,120
Then I'll help you arrange for horses.

185
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,250
That would be great.

186
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:30,820
Come on, everyone!

187
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,240
30 yuan for half an hour,

188
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,240
for horseback riding in our village,

189
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,320
it's the standard rate for everyone.

190
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:34,800
Okay?

191
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:35,760
Take care!

192
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,050
Enjoy your stay.

193
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:39,040
Welcome.

194
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,040
Come,

195
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:42,100
register here.

196
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,440
Take care.

197
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,410
Are you done with the painting?

198
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,640
Just finished.

199
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,140
I left some food on the windowsill

200
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,520
so you can grab a bite.

201
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,900
Mare's milk and barley cakes,

202
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,120
they help with sleep.

203
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,170
It actually suits my taste,

204
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,560
but I've always liked strong flavors.

205
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,760
What do you all think?

206
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:01,600
Ajala.

207
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,120
How's the taste for you?

208
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,080
So spicy!

209
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:05,760
Spicy!

210
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,200
I think...

211
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,880
I find it a bit salty,

212
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,520
but if you eat it with rice

213
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:13,580
or barley cakes, it's actually fine.

214
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,890
There's just one issue though,

215
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,320
it tastes great right off the stove,

216
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,840
but not so good when it gets cold.

217
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,440
And with the current weather,

218
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,680
dishes cool down quickly.

219
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,720
That's not a problem.

220
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,120
We can keep it warm with a flame underneath.

221
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:30,400
Considering people's varying tolerance for spice,

222
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,440
I think we should offer two flavors.

223
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:33,919
One mildly spicy,

224
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,460
and one regular spicy.

225
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:36,919
Good, let's do that.

226
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:38,960
Also,

227
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,299
I'm planning to set up our front yard,

228
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,760
get some outdoor tables and chairs,

229
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,440
sun shades, string lights,

230
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,640
fire pits and such.

231
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:50,040
Sister Ping, you're going all out!

232
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,280
The village is really

233
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:54,680
emphasizing the Peach Blossom Festival this time.

234
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:55,480
In life,

235
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,460
you need to seize opportunities.

236
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,360
For the comprehensive upgrade

237
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,240
of our courtyard's facilities,

238
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,010
I've decided

239
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,120
to increase the room rates by 30%.

240
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,040
That much?

241
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,600
